# Trading Platform Analysis Skill

This skill contains the comprehensive analysis and implementation plan for transforming the NSE index options trading platform into a production-grade, broker-agnostic, secure system.

## Overview

This document contains the complete analysis and implementation plan for transforming the NSE index options trading platform into a production-grade, broker-agnostic, secure system. It is updated as implementation progresses to allow resuming work after session loss.

## Initial Analysis (2026-05-08)

### System Strengths
- Excellent test coverage (1507+ tests passing)
- Comprehensive feature set (IV Rank, ML classifiers, risk management, etc.)
- Paper mode primary, live trading disabled by default
- Good documentation and clear configuration system
- Some modularization already in place (config, logging, datetime services extracted)

### Critical Areas Requiring Attention

#### 1. Security Vulnerabilities (Priority: Critical)
- Hardcoded secrets in config.json (BOT_TOKEN, CHAT_ID, api_key, access_token, password, totp_key, refresh_token, secret)
- Secrets potentially exposed in logs/error traces
- Missing authentication/authorization for administrative functions
- Insufficient input validation on external inputs (Telegram commands, web dashboard)

#### 2. Architectural Issues (Priority: High)
- Residual coupling between components despite some extraction
- Market data staleness risks with inconsistent freshness checks
- Hardcoded lot size assumptions (references to "50" scattered)
- Greeks calculation approximations in strike selection
- ML model predictions not properly integrated with regime-based signals

#### 3. Broker Abstraction Gaps (Priority: High)
- While BrokerPort interface exists, some methods may be incomplete in implementations
- Missing health monitoring and automatic reconnect with exponential backoff
- Lack of rate limiting to prevent API bans
- Missing idempotency keys for order placement
- Insufficient fill reconciliation and pending state handling

#### 4. Risk Management Enhancements (Priority: High)
- Missing real-time margin validation using broker APIs
- Need for liquidity checks beyond OI/volume (bid-ask spread analysis)
- Requirement for volatility-adjusted position sizing (VIX-based)
- Need for spread widening protection and slippage monitoring
- Drawdown-based position reduction not implemented

#### 5. ML/AI Improvements (Priority: Medium)
- Need for clean MlModelPort interface with multiple backend support
- Optional NVIDIA GPU acceleration support (not mandatory)
- Pre-inference feature schema validation
- Drift-to-retraining pipeline with validation gates
- Explainability integration (SHAP values) in signal confidence scoring
- Regime-aware models for different market conditions

#### 6. Observability & Monitoring (Priority: Medium)
- Need for correlation IDs throughout execution pipeline
- Contextual logging (trade_id, symbol, strategy, signal_id)
- Prometheus-compatible metrics collection
- Business metrics (win rate, P&L by strategy, signal latency)
- Infrastructure metrics (broker API latency, data freshness, queue depths)
- Health endpoints with deep dependency checks
- Alert routing to multiple channels (Telegram, email, webhook)
- Anomaly detection on key metrics

## Implementation Priority Order

### Phase 1: Foundation & Security (Week 1-2)
1. [X] Migrate all secrets to environment variables with OPBUYING_* prefix
2. [X] Implement secure credential storage (system keyring or encrypted vault)
3. [X] Add comprehensive input validation and audit logging
4. [X] Fix market data staleness detection with validation, caching, safe fallbacks
5. [X] Dynamic resolution of lot sizes, expiries, holidays, margin rules from authoritative sources

### Phase 2: Core Services Extraction (Week 3-4)
1. [x] Extract exception hierarchy and create custom exception types
2. [x] Extract shared models/core (Order, Position, Quote, Signal dataclasses)
3. [x] Complete notification service (Telegram handling with fallback/rate limiting)
4. [x] Complete persistence service (SQLite, JSON state, CSV with proper connection mgmt)
5. [x] Implement structured logging with correlation IDs and contextual logging

### Phase 3: Risk & Execution (Week 5-6)
1. [x] Extract risk service with margin validation and volatility-based sizing
2. [x] Implement execution service with idempotency and duplicate prevention
3. [x] Add comprehensive audit trail from signal to fill
4. [x] Implement broker health monitoring and failover mechanisms
5. [x] Add rate limiting and circuit breaker patterns for external dependencies

### Phase 4: ML/AI & Observability (Week 7-8)
1. [x] Create clean MlModelPort interface with multiple backend support
2. [x] Add local GPU acceleration support (optional NVIDIA/CUDA)
3. [x] Implement feature validation and drift-to-retraining pipeline
4. [x] Integrate explainability (SHAP values) into signal confidence scoring
5. [x] Implement Prometheus metrics collection and health endpoints
6. [x] Add distributed tracing for signal execution path
7. [x] Implement alert routing and anomaly detection

### Phase 5: Integration & Testing (Week 9-10)
1. [x] Wire up dependency injection container for all services
2. [x] Create comprehensive test suite with broker mocks and failure injection
3. [ ] Conduct security review and penetration testing
4. [ ] Validate paper→live readiness with manual approval process
5. [ ] Create deployment guides, operational runbooks, and final documentation

